-- Hyflux Unit Signs Loan to Buy Desalination Equipment From Mitsui
-- B y   R a n d a l l   H a c k l e y   a n d   K y u n g   B o k   C h o
-- 2012-06-14T16:12:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-14/hyflux-unit-signs-loan-to-buy-desalination-equipment-from-mitsui.html
Hyflux Ltd. (HYF)  said today that its
Hydrochem unit signed a $14.4 million loan with the Japan Bank
for International Cooperation and  Mizuho Corporate Bank  to
purchase desalination plant equipment from Mitsui & Co.  The loan is for the Tuaspring plant, one of Asia’s largest
seawater reverse osmosis desalination facilities in western
Singapore that’s scheduled to start operations in July 2013.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Randall Hackley in Zurich at 
